The Chief Press Secretary to Gov. Darius Ishaku of Taraba, Hassan Mijinyawa, who was abducted on January 30 has been released by his abductors. Mr Bala Dan -Abu, the Senior Special Assistant to the Governor on Media and Publicity confirmed this to newsmen on Sunday in Jalingo. He said the CPS was released in the late hours of Saturday and had been reunited with his family. The senior special assistant said no ransom was paid for his release and the CPS was hale and hearty.